text: Quitman County is a county in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 6,176 people lived there. Its county seat is Marks. The county is named after John A. Quitman, Governor of Mississippi from 1835 to 1836 and from 1850 to 1851. Quitman County is in the Mississippi Delta region of Mississippi. == References == Category:1870s establishments in Mississippi Category:1877 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
